data.LN: Loan Number - A unique number used to identify a loan on a property, entity, or location at a financial institution or mortgage broker
data.M3: Disbursing Station - DOD Disbursing Offices (location and address) can be identified by a unique number found in departmental regulations
data.M4: Department of Defense Routing Identifier Code (RIC) - An integral and predetermined participant in an established logistical system performing general logistic control, distribution, and storage functions
data.MC: Medicaid Provider Number - Number assigned to a health care provider for submitting claims covered by Medicaid benefits
data.MD: Manitoba Department of Mines and Resources
data.ML: Multiple Listing Service Vendor - Multiple Listing Service Identification
data.MP: Medicare Provider Number - Number assigned to a health care provider for submitting claims covered by Medicare benefits
data.MR: Medicaid Recipient Identification Number - Unique identification number assigned to each member covered under a subscriber's contract
data.NA: National Association of Realtors - Multiple Listing Service Identification
data.NI: National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC) Identification
data.NO: National Criminal Information Center Originating Agency
data.PC: Provider Commercial Number - Unique number assigned to the provider for submitting claims to commercial insurance carriers
data.PP: Pharmacy Processor Number - Unique number assigned to each pharmacy for submitting claims
data.RA: Regulatory Agency Number - A number assigned to a regulatory jurisdiction
data.SD: Saskatchewan Department of Energy Mines and Resources
data.SF: Suffix Code - A code assigned by a regulatory agency to operator numbers
data.SL: State License Number - Number uniquely issued to provider by state licensing board
data.SP: Specialty License Number - License number issued to identify providers unique area of practice
data.SW: Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications (SWIFT) Address
data.UL: UCC/EAN Location Code - A globally unique 13 digit code for the identification of a legal, functional or physical location within the Uniform Code Council (UCC) and International Article Number Association (EAN) numbering system
data.UM: UCC/EAN Location Code Suffix - The last part of a 13 digit UCC/EAN Location Code within the Uniform Code Council (UCC) and International Number Association (EAN) numbering system; A 3 to 10 digit code for the identification of a location within the company identified by the UCC/EAN Location Code Prefix
data.UP: Unique Physician Identification Number (UPIN) - Number assigned to the provider by the National Registry for Medicare identification purposes
data.XV: Health Care Financing Administration National Payer Identification Number (PAYERID)
data.XX: Health Care Financing Administration National Provider Identifier
data.ZY: Temporary Identification Number - A temporary ID to be used until a permanent ID is processed
